## Worktree Settings (optional)

> Override `/craft:execute` worktree defaults if the project needs different paths
> or branch naming. Both are optional — when omitted, the defaults below apply.

- **Worktree path pattern:** `../<repo>-worktrees/<slice-id>-<slug>/` (default)
- **Branch name pattern:** `<slice-id>-<slug>` (default)

> Because worktrees live outside the project root, `/craft:execute` adds their
> shared **base directory** (derived from the path pattern above) to
> `permissions.additionalDirectories` in `.claude/settings.local.json` on first
> run — once, after a confirmation — so subagents working inside worktrees don't
> trigger per-path permission prompts. Idempotent; existing permissions are
> merged, never overwritten; the file stays gitignored. Change the pattern here
> and the next run trusts the new base.

## Self-Verification Settings (optional)

Override `/debug`, `/craft:review`, and stale-slice defaults if needed.

- **Max attempts:** 5
- **Auto-trigger threshold:** 2
- **Token brake during loop:** 15000
- **Stale slice threshold:** 7 days
- **Review in-phase fix cap:** 5

## Agent Model Overrides (optional)

> Override CRAFT subagent models (defaults in plugin's `model-defaults.md`).
> Allowed: `opus`, `sonnet`, `haiku`, `inherit`. Resolution: agent frontmatter →
> this section. `/craft:prime` reports the effective model and soft-warns on
> invalid entries.

